The paper deals with signal processing and estimation in wireless communication systems, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of 1-bit quantization and the need for efficient processing methods suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of blind direction-of-arrival (DOA) parameter estimation with an array of sensors suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine vision (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SI).
